The paper discusses the limitations of perfect security in steganographic systems, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions information theory (cs.IT) and uses English words and acronyms for hiding information, which relates to multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes an enhancement to the steganographic scheme, which could potentially involve computer vision (cs.CV).
